Preconditions:
- The input array `candies` is not null.
- The length of the input array `candies` is greater than or equal to 1.
- Each element in the input array `candies` is a positive integer.
- The input integer `k` is a positive integer.

Postconditions:
- The output is an integer representing the maximum number of candies each child can get.
- Each child receives the same number of candies.
- Each child can take at most one pile of candies.
- Some piles of candies may go unused.